<br>
Harte was concerned.  Norrath had been at peace these many long months with only the natural evils to combat.  His guild's path had been shining brightly and their many achievements had inspired many adventurers to admit that they carried the stones in their heart.  Good-will, celebration and riches had blessed not only his guild, but many others as well.  These were grand days across Norrath.<br>
<br>
Hungry, Harte nibbled on some carrots that he had foraged earlier, as he thought of the event that might change this peaceful world.  It seemed that one mighty guild of adventurers had again slighted an equally strong alliance of guilds.  The peace, understanding and structure that led to peace across Norrath was again threatened by this action.  Could this be the beginning of the foretold &quot;Days of Plunder&quot;?<br>
<br>
As the gnome called out that the boat approached, Harte thought of his many friends who were members of this guild thumbing their noses at the community around them.  The officers didn't consider the friendships their members had outside the guild, only of the riches that they could steal.  Not riches they couldn't get anyway, over time, riches they felt they must have right then.  Harte was concerned, for the most rewarding thing in Norrath were the friendships nurtured over many ages.  He wondered and worried whether he'd ever be able to adventure with these friends again and felt again the sorrow over old dear friends lost to similar actions in the past.<br>
<br>
As he boarded the boat, he paused.  Listening to the silence of the vast desert, he wondered how long that peaceful quiet would last.  Muttering under his breath, he stepped onto the boat, <br>
<br>
&quot;Will they never learn?&quot; <p>Harte Greyeagle<BR>
Surefall Druid, Tribunal Server<BR>
